Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setBudgetingMode(25.10)                                setBudgetingMode(25.10)

Name
       setBudgetingMode - Sets the timing budgeting mode

Syntax
       setBudgetingMode

       [-help]

       [-abutted {true|false}]

       [-accumulated {true|false}]

       [-boundaryConditionTemplatePath <directory_path>]

       [-bufferDelayLibCell <libname>/<cellname>]

       [-bufferDelaySelectionEffort {low|high|none}]

       [-ccd {true|false}]

       [-constantModel {true|false}]

       [-distributeMMMC {true|false}]

       [-dontWriteWireLoad {true|false}]

       [-driveConstraint {drive | drive_cell | input_transition}]

       [-fixTopLevelPaths {none|all|negativeOnly|positiveOnly}]

       [-handleComplexSDC {true|false}]

       [-honorPortBoundaryCondition {true|false}]

       [-honorPortDelays {true|false}]

       [-honorReportTimingFormat {true|false}]

       [-ignoreDontTouch {true|false}]

       [-includeLatency {true|false}]

       [-includeWireLoadsInLib {true|false}]

       [-inputLoad {true|false}]

       [-justify {delay|exception|lib_arc|boundary_condition|all}]

       [-justifyBudgetDir <directory_name>]

       [-keepPinListsForBlockPorts {true|false}]

       [-latencyOnClocks {true|false}]

       [-localLatency {true|false}]

       [-localUncertainty {true|false}]

       [-makeNegativeInputDelayZero {true | false}]

       [-makeReducedTimingGraph {true | false}]

       [-masterClone {masterOnly|merged|uniqueViewPerHInst}]

       [-noFalsePathsForUnCstrPorts {true|false}]

       [-noSetupView {true|false}]

       [-noHoldView {true|false}]

       [-reportOrModifyBudget {true|false}]

       [-reset]

       [-rptNegSlackOnPorts <value>]

       [-sdcContents {full | pushDownOnly | boundaryConstraintsOnly | noBound-
       aryCondition | noBoundaryConstraints}]

       [-stageBasedFanoutDrivingFactor <value>]

       [-stageBasedPartitionMultiplier {{HInst1 m1} {HInst2 m2}..}]

       [-stageBasedWeight {S  | C  | B}]

       [-useBoundaryCondition {optimized | template | actual | empty}]

       [-virtualClock {true|false}]

       [-virtualOptEngine {none|earlyTimingEngine|proto}]

       [-writeConstraintsForClkOutputPorts {true|false}]

       [-writeFPForHold {true|false}]

       [-writeLatencyPerClock {true|false}]

       Sets  the  timing  budgeting mode. This command governs the way budgets
       are derived and saved. All parameters relevant to  saving  or  deriving
       can be specified with this command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each setBudgetingMode parameter. For a  detailed
              description  of  the command and all its parameters, use the man
              command:

              man setBudgetingMode

       -abutted {true | false}
              Specifies that the software abuts the partitions when allocating
              budgets from positive slack  paths.  With  this  parameter,  the
              software  assumes  that all partitions are abutted and therefore
              the software does not allocate extra delay at the top-level.

              Default: false

              Note: The software automatically handles the abutted  partitions
              (both  partial and full) even when you do not specify this para-
              meter.

       -accumulated {true | false}
              Generates SDC for lower-level hierarchy child partition  in  the
              .lib and flat forms (L3 as shown in the example below). The fol-
              lowing example also presents the matrix to understand the behav-
              ior of the -accumulated parameter at different levels of hierar-
              chy:

              With the help of the -accumulated parameter, SDC supports gener-
              ation  of constraints in the specified child partition through a
              Tcl variable-enabled conditional loop, as shown below:

              if {$budget_use_accumulated != 1}{

                #Constraints considering child partition in the .lib form

              } else {

                #Constraints considering child partition in the flat form

              }

              Note:

              * A single viewDefinition.tcl or SDC file can support  both  the
                .lib  or  flat  flows.  This  is because there are conditional
                loops in the viewDefinition.tcl and SDC files.

              * Conditional loops are controlled by a Tcl variable named  bud-
                get_use_accumulated. The default value of this Tcl variable is
                0,  which specified that constraints will be processed consid-
                ering the child partition in the .lib form. You  need  to  run
                set  budget_use_accumulated  1  before  loading the design for
                processing the constraints considering the child partition  in
                the flat form.

              * This  parameter  does not impact the output of the viewDefini-
                tion.tcl and SDC files for the bottom-most partitions.

              Default: false

       -boundaryConditionTemplatePath <directory_path>
              Specifies the directory path containing the model  files  to  be
              used  for  generating  template-based boundary condition through
              the -useBoundaryCondition template parameter. Hence, the -bound-
              aryConditionTemplatePath parameter allows you  to  specify  your
              own template file for generating boundary conditions.

              The  directory  path  specified  with this parameter should have
              boundary model files for each view with the file name format  as
              view_name.model. If the model files are missing for any view, an
              error  is  prompted.  If a view is both setup and hold, the same
              model will be used.

              Default: ""

       -bufferDelayLibCell <libname/cellname>
              Specifies the buffer that should be used for virtual buffer  ad-
              justment.

              Default: ""

       -bufferDelaySelectionEffort {low|high|none}
              Controls the virtual buffer selection effort for calculating the
              buffer delay adjustment. The three effort levels are:

              * low: Uses buffer selection algorithm based on drive strength.

              * high:  Uses  buffer  selection  algorithm  based on actual one
                buffer delay.

              * none: Disables buffer delay adjustment.

              Use the low/high value of this parameter to enable buffer  delay
              adjustment.  Additionally,  you  can use the -bufferDelayLibCell
              parameter with the libname/cellname value  for  enabling  buffer
              delay  adjustment. When both the -bufferDelaySelectionEffort and
              -bufferDelayLibCell parameters are set, -bufferDelayLibCell  has
              more precedence.

              Default: none

       -ccd {true|false}
              Generates  scripts  for  verification  of time budgeting top and
              block constraints against pre-budget chip constraints using  the
              Conformal Constraint Designer software.

              Default: false

       -constantModel {true|false}
              Specifies  the  type of timing model created. The -constantModel
              parameter specifies that constant timing models are created.

              Default: true

       -distributeMMMC{true|false}
              When set to true, it enables distributed timing  budgeting.  Use
              setDistributeHost  -custom -custom_script {LSF command} to setup
              LSF machine to distribute jobs. The -custom_script  accepts  the
              bsub  command as input with all its parameters. Use the -K para-
              meter of the bsub command to run it.

              The -resource parameter of the setDistributeHost command for the
              LSF string is not supported by the -distributeMMMC parameter, as
              it cannot generate complete command. Only the -custom_script pa-
              rameter is supported.

              If the setDistributeHost command is not specified, the jobs  run
              on the local machine.

              Default: false

       -dontWriteWireLoad {true|false}
              Writes  out the set_load command with the -wire_load information
              for the output pins in the generated SDC file, if the design  is
              routed.

              Default: false

       -driveConstraint {drive | drive_cell | input_transition}
              Determines  the  boundary condition for the input ports. If this
              parameter is not specified, set_driving_cell is written, by  de-
              fault. Specify one of the following values with this parameter:

              * drive:  Generates the boundary drive information for the input
                ports in the budgeted  SDC  file,  using  the  set_drive  con-
                straint.

              * drive_cell:   Generates the boundary drive information for the
                input ports in the  budgeted  SDC  file,  using  the  set_dri-
                ving_cell constraint.

              * input_transition: Generates the boundary drive information for
                input  ports  in  the  budgeted  SDC  file,  using the set_in-
                put_transition constraint.

              Default: drive_cell

       -fixTopLevelPaths {none | all | negativeOnly | positiveOnly}
              Fixes the top-level timing budget and proportions the  remaining
              timing  budget  only  for  the partitions based on the specified
              value. Use one of the following parameter values:

              * none: Performs the default proportionate budgeting.

              * all: Fixes the top-level timing budget and proportions the re-
                maining budget only for the partitions.

              * negativeOnly: Fixes the top-level timing  budget  and  propor-
                tions  the  remaining budget only for the partitions for nega-
                tive slack paths.

              * positiveOnly: Fixes the top-level timing  budget  and  propor-
                tions  the  remaining budget only for the partitions for posi-
                tive slack paths.

              Default: none

       -handleComplexSDC {true|false}
              Specifies to use Common Timing Engine's  write_sdc  command  for
              ensuring  proper  push  down in case of using nested/complex SDC
              constraints. The software saves SDC for each view from the  cur-
              rent session, which is used for budgeting. Use it in the follow-
              ing cases:

              * Constraints are specified interactively by the user.

              * There are regular expressions in the SDC constraints.

              * A TCL command (like foreach) is used in the SDC constraints.

              A  limitation  while  using  this  parameter  is that in case of
              netlist reduction, some SDC file  constraints  that  get  pushed
              down normally, will not be pushed down.

              Writing  SDCs  while using this parameter may increase the turn-
              around time.

              Default: false

       -honorPortBoundaryCondition {true|false}
              When set to true, deriveTimingBudget pushes  down  the  boundary
              conditions  from  the  chip IO ports to the block IO ports. This
              parameter works only in the cases where the block IO  ports  are
              directly  connected to the chip IO ports (when there is no logic
              in between the chip and block, and there is no dependency on the
              abutted condition).

              When this parameter is set to its default value, true, following
              is the behavior for those partition ports,  which  are  directly
              connected to the top level ports:

              * For  the  actual and optimized boundary condition mode, if the
                boundary conditions are specified in the chip  SDC,  they  are
                written as is. Else, nothing is written.

              * For the template boundary condition mode, if the boundary con-
                ditions are specified in the chip SDC, they are written as is.
                Else, the existing template-based method is used for them.

              If  you  turn off this parameter, there will be no change in the
              behavior of any partition port, whether or not  it  is  directly
              connected.

              Default: true

       -honorPortDelays {true|false}
              When  this  parameter  is set to true, deriveTimingBudget repli-
              cates the chip IO SID/SOD values to block IO, if these  two  are
              directly connected and abut each other.

              Default: true

       -honorReportTimingFormat {true|false}
              Honors  the  global  variable  set through set_globalreport_tim-
              ing_format by the user in the justification reports,  which  are
              generated  through  deriveTimingBudget,  when  the setBudgetMode
              -justify parameter is specified. This parameter keeps justifica-
              tion reports and columns of report_timing in the same format  as
              set by the user.

              This  parameter may impact the turnaround time of the deriveTim-
              ingBudget command, when the setBudgetMode -justify parameter  is
              specified.

              Default: true

       -ignoreDontTouch {true|false}
              Specifies  the handling of don't touch (fixed) objects . The pa-
              rameter allows you to modify these objects also.

              Default: false

       -includeLatency {true|false}
              Specifies whether the clock latency is included in  the  set_in-
              put_delay and set_output_delay constraints.

              Note:  The  clock  latency  is always included if the design has
              propagated clock(s) irrespective of this parameter.

              set_input_delay and set_output_delay change and are based on ac-
              tual arrival times.

              Default: true

       -inputLoad {true|false}
              Specifies whether the set_load constraints have  to  be  written
              for input pins in the generated SDC file. With this option, load
              constraint on ports is specified.

              Default: false

       -includeWireLoadsInLib {true|false}
              Specifies to include the wire loads in library model pin capaci-
              tance  to handle high interface net loads. It provides extra in-
              formation in .lib file for more accurate modelling.

              Default: false

       -justify {delay|exception|lib_arc|boundary_condition|all}
              Controls the type of justification and also decides  whether  or
              not  to  generate  the justification reports. You may use one or
              more of the following values with this parameter:

              * delay: Budget justification files for  all  the  partition  IO
                ports are generated.

              * exception: Budget justification files for all the partition IO
                ports are generated with exception data.

              * lib_arc: Justification files for libs are generated.

              * boundary_condition:  Justification files for the boundary con-
                ditions used in the constraint files are generated.

              * all: All the justification files are generated.

              Note: When this parameter is used without any value, no justifi-
              cation files are generated. Only the summary is generated.

              Default: ""

       -justifyBudgetDir <directory_name>
              Directs output of budget justification to the  specified  direc-
              tory and dumps the summary files.

              Default: budget justify

       -keepPinListsForBlockPorts{true|false}
              Specifies to preserve all fan-in and fan-out pin lists for block
              ports.

              The default value is true. When set to true, the runtime will be
              the  fastest  but involves high memory usage. The value of false
              means that the peak memory consumed will decrease  but  with  an
              increase in runtime.

              You  can  use  this  parameter to control memory consumption and
              runtime for budgeting processes. It does not affect other  func-
              tions when specified.

              Default:true

       -latencyOnClocks {true|false}
              Writes the set_clock_latency constraint on the clocks instead of
              ports  in  the  generated SDC files. Use this parameter when you
              have multiple clocks on the same port.

              Default: Writes the set_clock_latency constraint on the ports.

              Default: true

       -localLatency {true|false}
              Adjusts the set_clock_latency constraint  information  that  you
              specify  using  the setPtnUserCnsFile command to the constraints
              file generated after budgeting.

              When you specify this parameter, the software checks whether the
              set_clock_latency constraint specifies a clock or a port.

              If the constraint specifies a clock and the clock exists in  the
              partition,  then the constraint is added to the constraints file
              generated after budgeting. If the clock does not  exist  in  the
              partition, the software does not write out the constraint.

              If  the  constraint specifies a port, the constraint is added to
              the constraints file generated after budgeting.

              The source latency is calculated as follows:

              source latency = top-level source latency  +  top-level  network
              latency - local network latency

              Default: false

       -localUncertainty {true | false}
              Adds  the  set_clock_uncertainty constraint information that you
              specify using the setPtnUserCnsFile command to  the  constraints
              file generated after budgeting.

              When you use this parameter, the constraint file generated after
              budgeting  has  input and output delays using virtual clocks in-
              stead of real clocks in the SDC file. The software uses the vir-
              tual clocks to differentiate the clock uncertainty for  external
              paths (paths that are coming from or going to the top-level) and
              internal paths of the partition.

       -makeNegativeInputDelayZero {true | false}
              Specifies to adjust negative set input delay to 0.

              Default: true

       -makeReducedTimingGraph {true | false}
              When  set to true, this parameter enables ART during timing bud-
              geting. When set to false (default value), it skips running  ART
              during  timing  budgeting to avoid constraints from dropping un-
              necessarily.

              Default: false

       -masterClone {masterOnly|merged|uniqueViewPerHInst}
              Specifies how the constraints are generated for master and clone
              designs. Following is the description of the parameter values:

              * masterOnly:  Derives  budgets  only  for  the  master   parti-
                tion/inst.

              * merged:  Derives  budgets based on the worst case data per pin
                for the master and all its clones.

              * uniqueViewPerHInst: For partitioned block,  creates  a  corre-
                sponding  view  for  each  instance  of the master and all its
                clones, where timing  constraints  are  generated  considering
                this  instance timing separately. So total number of new views
                in block viewDefination.tcl is equal number of instances  mul-
                tiflied  with  the  number of views. For partitioned TOPs .lib
                model, the "merged" approach is followed. So that there  would
                be  only  one .lib per view for every partition. No additional
                views are created for partitioned TOP.

              Default: masterOnly

       -noFalsePathsForUnCstrPorts {true|false}
              Specifies not to create false paths for unconstrained ports.

              Default: false

               -noHoldView {true|false}   " Specifies to derive  budgets  only
              for  setup  views.  Dummy files are created for the hold view as
              budgeting is not done for them.

              Default: false

       -noSetupView {true|false}
              Specifies to derive budgets only for hold views. Dummy files are
              created for the setup view as budgeting is not done for them.

              Default: false

       -reportOrModifyBudget {true | false}
              Specifies to enable the collection of data required to use  the-
              modifyBudget  command.  You  must  specify this parameter before
              budgeting to run modifyBudget later in the flow.

              If this parameter is not  specified,  the  modifyBudget  command
              does not produce any results.

              Default: false

       -reset Resets  parameters to their default values. The -reset parameter
              must be the first parameter specified. If you specify -reset  by
              itself,  the  software resets all setBudgetingMode parameters to
              their default values. If you specify  parameters  after  -reset,
              the  software resets only those parameters to their default val-
              ues.  Any values that do not already match the default value and
              are reset. will be reported.

       -rptNegSlackOnPorts <value>
              Reports if partition ports have a slack less than the  specified
              value and saves this information in the .warn file. The slack is
              calculated  based  on  data  arrival time and clock time at data
              sampling points. The report is saved to the .warn file.

              Default: -1e+06

       -sdcContents {full | pushDownOnly | boundaryConstraintsOnly | noBound-
       aryCondition | noBoundaryConstraints}
              Determines the contents of timing budgeted  SDCs.  You  can  set
              only  one of the following permissible enum values of this para-
              meter at a time:

              * full: Generates the default SDC.

              *

                pushDownOnly: Generates SDC with only pushdown constraints for
                the block partitions. Pushdown constraints are applied to only
                those paths, which are completely inside a partition. By  con-
                sidering  only  the pushdown constraints, this parameter value
                ignores the constraints applied on partition  interface  paths
                from full chip SDC.

                When  this  parameter  value  is specified in the early design
                phase, the reg-to-IO and IO-to-reg paths are ignored. In  such
                cases,  timing  constraints  are generated for only reg-to-reg
                paths.

              * boundaryConstraintsOnly: Generates SDC with only set_input_de-
                lay, set_output_delay, and other boundary conditions for ports
                (such as set_load and set_drive). The  SDC  generated  through
                this  parameter  value will also include commands to reset old
                constraints while initiating the re-budgeting.

              * noBoundaryCondition: Generates SDC without any boundary condi-
                tions for ports (such as set_load and set_drive). Except this,
                all other constraints are included, when this parameter  value
                is specified.

              * noBoundaryConstraints:  Generates SDC without set_input_delay,
                set_output_delay, and  other  boundary  conditions  for  ports
                (such  as set_load and set_drive). Except this, all other con-
                straints are included, when this parameter value is specified.

              Default: full

       -stageBasedFanoutDrivingFactor <value>
              Specifies the fanout count of the pin, according  to  which  the
              buffer stages are added in the timing graph. This parameter pro-
              vides  the  basis  for  the  software to calculate the number of
              fanouts and buffer stages to be virtually added for  each  stage
              according to the following table:

              Fanout Range                  Number of Buffer Stafe Added (n):1
              to d1 to d                                        0

              (d+1) to d2                                         1

              (d2+1) to d3                                       2

              (d3+1) to d4                                       3

              If the weight of the original cell is w, weight of the buffer is
              b, and the number of buffer stages is n, then:

              Final weight of cell = w + (b*n)

              See  the  example below for understanding the functioning of the
              -stageBasedFanoutDrivingFactor parameter.

              setBudgetingMode -stageBasedWeight {3 2 1}

              Default: -1

       -stageBasedPartitionMultiplier {{HInst1 m1} {HInst2 m2}..}
              Specifies the weight multiplication  factor  for  the  partition
              hinsts.  Those  hInsts, which are not explicitly mentioned, will
              have the default weights. If the weights  of  hinsts  have  been
              specified  using  the setBudgetingMode -stageBasedWeight parame-
              ter, those are used with their default weights.  Else,  the  de-
              fault  weights (1 for sequential cell, 1 for combinational cell,
              and 0 for buffer/inverter) are used. In case  of  nested  parti-
              tions,  if  the  child partition multiplier is not specified ex-
              plicitly, then it will have its parent's multiplier.  If  parent
              and  child  partitions have separate multipliers, then they will
              be honored.

              See the example below for understanding the usage of this  para-
              meter:

              setBudgetingMode -stageBasedWeight {2 1 1}

              setBudgetingMode  -stageBasedPartitionMultiplier {{PTN1 2} {PTN2
              3}}

              Cycle time = T

              Budget for PTN1= 8/19 T

              Budget for PTN2= 9/19 T

              Budget for top = 2/19 T

              Default: ""

       -stageBasedWeight {S  | C  | B}
              Specifies default weights of the sequential, combinational,  and
              buffer/inverter cells for the stage-based timing budgeting. Fol-
              lowing are the default weights of these cells:

              * Sequential: 1

              * Combinational: 1

              * Buffer/inverter: 1

              Default: {1 1 1}

       -useBoundaryCondition {optimized|template|actual|empty}
              Specifies the criteria for choosing boundary conditions. Follow-
              ing are the usages of the parameter values:

              * optimized:  The values of boundary conditions are fetched from
                the engine used to build timing graph. If the engine does  not
                provide  any  values,  than the template is used automatically
                and a warning is displayed indicating that no optimized bound-
                ary conditions are available, and the template is  used  auto-
                matically.  For example, -useBoundaryCondition {optimized} for
                -virtulaOptEngine {proto | none} will display such a warning.

              * template: The values of boundary conditions are derived  auto-
                matically and used through the default template.

                Note:    The    default    templates   are   saved   as   bud-
                get_model/<view_name>.model.

              * actual: Uses the actual netlist to build the timing graph.

              * empty: No boundary condition is dumped.

              Default: template

       -virtualClock {true|false}
              When set to false, this parameter prevents creation of new  vir-
              tual  clocks  during  timing  budgeting.  The software takes the
              worst path into account and provides the minimum  required  time
              amongst  all  the  paths  passing through a port. Since there is
              only a single critical path, no virtual clock is created.

              While using this parameter:

              * For an endpoint with both  single-cycle  and  multicycle  con-
                straints, multicycle constraints are not defined.

              * At  the  partition  level,  a path which is constrained before
                budgeting, is not unconstrained after budgeting.

              * If a path has both single and multi-cycle constraints,  single
                cycle constraint is retained, and hence, the path is optimized
                accordingly and timing closure is not affected.

              Following is an example of -virtualClock true:

              Following is an example of -virtualClock false:

              Default: true

       -virtualOptEngine {none|earlyTimingEngine|proto}
              Specifies the virtual optimization engine to be used. The values
              of this parameter include:

              none

              Specifies that the timing graph is generated through report_tim-
              ing.

              earlyTimingEngine

              Specifies that the timing graph is generated by optVirtual -ear-
              lyTimingEngine.

              proto

              Specifies  that  the timing graph is generated by prototype tim-
              ing.

              Default: none

              Note: User can use ART (createActiveLogicView -type  timing_bud-
              get) before generating the timing graph to reduce TAT and memory
              during budgeting flow.

       -writeConstraintsForClkOutputPorts {true|false}
              Specifies to write extra constraints on the output port of block
              SDC.

       When  this  parameter is specified, the following extra constraints are
       written out:

              * set_clock_sense - this constraint is dumped if  the  clock  is
                used as data going forward after partition

              * create_generated_clock  -  this  constraint  is  dumped if the
                clock is used as clock going forward after partition

              If the clock is used as both data and clock going  forward,  the
              parameter does not write out these extra constraints.

              Default: false

       -writeFPForHold {true|false}
              Writes  false_path  -hold constraints for all I/Os when deriving
              timing budgets in setup mode.

              For inputs, the saveTimingBudget command  writes  the  following
              constraint:

              set_false_path -from port -hold

              For  outputs,  the saveTimingBudget command writes the following
              constraint:

              set_false_path -to port -hold

              Default: false

       -writeLatencyPerClock {true|false}
              Specifies to write latency per clock instead of per  port.  When
              you set this variable to true,  set_clock_latency is written per
              clock  if  multiple  clocks enter the partition through the same
              port.

              Default: false

Examples
              * The following set of commands load database for timing budget-
                ing:

                setBudgetingMode -stageBasedWeight {3 2 1}

                setBudgetingMode  -stageBasedPartitionMultiplier   {{PTN1   2}
                {PTN2 3}}

                setBudgetingMode -stageBasedFanoutDrivingFactor 8

                deriveTimingBudget -stageBased

              * The  following  command  sets  the input and output budgets to
                3000:

                setBudgetingMode -snapInputBudget 3000 -snapOutputBudget 3000

                The resulting message appear in the .warn file when you gener-
                ate budgets.

                /* Start Section: Pin  constraint  values  less  than  defined
                threshold time

                (setup)*/

                Input Threshold Value: 3.000

                Output Threshold Value: 3.000

                Constraint:  set_output_delay  11.524 -clock {CLK2} -max -rise
                [get_ports {sub1_out1}]

                allocates block delay less than input threshold time.

                Block delay: 0.476

                Constraint: set_output_delay 11.524 -clock {CLK2}  -max  -fall
                [get_ports {sub1_out1}]

                allocates block delay less than input threshold time.

                Block delay: 0.476

                /*  End  Section:  Pin  constraint  values  less  than defined
                threshold time (setup)*/

                justifyBudget header example:

                Budgeted constraint type: set_output_delay(setup rise)

                Initial budget available time = 12.000

                One Buffer Delay for Adjustment(cell ssiv): 1.000

                Fixed Delay for Feedthrough Paths(fixFdThru)= (2  x  1.000)  =
                2.000

                External Segment Fixed Delay From Budget Snap(snapExtFixedDel)
                = 5.000

                Total External Segment Fixed Delay(extFixDel) = 5.000

                This  Block's  Segment  Fixed  Delay from budget snap(snapInt-
                FixedDel) = 1.000

                Total This Block's Segment Fixed Delay(intFixDel) = 1.000

                External Segment Extra Delay From Budget  Snap  (snapExtDelEx-
                tra) = 2.000

                This  Block's Extra Delay From Budget Snap (snapIntDelExtra) =
                1.000

                Path Extra Delay From Budget Snap (snapExtraDel)  =  (2.000  +
                1.000) = 3.000

                Fixed Delay on the Path(pathFixDel) = (5.000 + 1.000 + 1.000 +
                2.000) = 9.000

                Fixed Delay Adjustment(fixDel)= 9.000

                Clock Skew(clkSkew): 0.000

                Adjustment for budget available time= -(pathFixDel + fixFdThru
                - clkSkew + snapExtraDel)

                = -(6.000 + 2.000 - 0.000 + 3.000)

                = -11.000

                Available   budget  after  adjustments(AvailTime)=  (12.000  -
                11.000) = 1.000

                External Segment Delay(extSegDel): 8.000

                This Block's Segment Delay(segDel): 0.000

                Total delay(totDel): 8.000 + 0.000 = 8.000

                Virtual Clock Adjustment(virClk): 0.000

                Budgeted constraint = AvailTime * extSegDel / totDel +  fixDel
                + virClk + startClkLat

                Budgeted  constraint = 1.000 * 8.000 / 8.000 + 9.000 + 0.000 +
                0.000 = 10.000

